  "prompt": "Why did Pepper Potts leave Tony Stark in Captain America: Civil War? Why wasn\u2019t she in the film?",
  "response": "Pepper Potts, played by Gwyneth Paltrow, did not leave Tony Stark in Captain America: Civil War. However, she did not appear in the film because her character was taking a break from her relationship with Tony Stark.\n\nIn the Marvel Cinematic Universe, Pepper and Tony's relationship had been through many ups and downs. In Iron Man 3, they had a significant moment where Pepper nearly died, which put a strain on their relationship. By the time of Captain America: Civil War, Pepper had decided to take a break from their relationship to focus on her own life and career.\n\nThis break was mentioned in the film when Tony Stark talks to Captain America about his personal life. Tony mentions that he and Pepper are \"taking a break\" and that it's \"probably for the best right now.\"\n\nSo, while Pepper did not leave Tony in the context of the film, her absence was explained as a temporary break in their relationship.",
